u only have to achieve your 17</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8.67pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt"> Edition exam and pass two installation inspections. If you look on the various</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt"> forums around the internet, the forums are loaded with people who have just passed their 17</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8.67pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt"> edition exam and are now looking to be told how to carry out two installs to pass the Part P compliance inspections from the NICEIC or Elecsa etc etc.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">In my vie</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">w Part P is self defeating. It does absolutely nothing to improve electrical safety. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">Let’s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt"> look at a few other major problems.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">Firstly, when a job has been completed that is required to be notified under the part p scheme, the only details required are t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">he name and address of the customer as well as sticking a check box to indicate what type of work was carried out.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">So what we are allowing is under qualified people to carry out electrical design, installation and testing and then require no design or tes</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">ting parameters to be submitted for scrutiny by someone who does possess the required competence.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">In fact, Part P seems to be more of a licence for people who have no competence to easily gain accreditation and carry out dangerous and shoddy work legally.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">We have licensed the cowboys.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">There is a vicious cycle out there right now. That vicious cycle goes as follows:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">Government creates legal licence for cowboys to operate</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">Cowboy meets potential victim and does not have the design knowledge to price the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">job correctly to achieve a safe, compliant installation</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">Customer decides to buy on price</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">Electrician makes light bulb work</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">Customer has no idea electrician has installed a potential fire risk due to incorrect design</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">Customer has no idea metal light fit</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">ting has not been</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt"> earthed or the modified circuit does not meet other requirements such as disconnection times in the event of a fault</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">Electrician is not required to submit design details</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">Problem remains until either house burns down, house is sold and te</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">sted or customer is killed</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">Highly competent electrician who priced the job correctly looses business and eventually goes bust or moves in to employment</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">General public are left with a mass of cowboys ready to serve with few quality electricians left</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">I w</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">ould invite anyone of the committee to come and work with me for a two month period to experience firsthand</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt"> the effect this has on people’s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt"> lives and the dangers out there that exist.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">You only have to look at the statistics for death, injury and fires cau</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">sed by electricity. I believe that if the system continues as it is these statistics will rise </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">The biggest flaw of all is the fact that there is no mechanism to ensure that work is carried out properly. Time and time again I work for people who have jus</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">t bought a house. I test and inspect the house and find significant problems.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">There are too many vested interests and mortgage companies and estate agents are two massive culprits in my view.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">I believe that there shouyld be a mechanism where before any </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">house is sold, an independent third party electrical inspector should inspect the property and any defects taken off the price of the house.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">DIY home owners are getting away with carrying out dangerous electrical work on a massive scale. The problem is ex</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">acerbated by incompetent electricians, desperate for money who will then come in and sign off the work. Sometimes knowingly sometimes through sheer incompetence.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">I want to share one last story with you.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">I was recently tasked with solving a customer’s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt"> elec</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">trical problem. The problem was the young couple were experiencing blown light bulbs, up to 2 a day at times.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">What I found was a trail of destruction. I believe what happened there (after speaking with the next door neighbour) was the home owner rewired t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">he house himself.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">This couple bought the house and thought the house wiring was fine because they had a Part P compliance certificate. Unfortunately a Napit engineer who had installed the consumer unit was clearly incompetent. I took one look at the test </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">results and could not understand some of the data he had recorded.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">He had not carried out any proper testing or inspection, in fact</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt"> I believe he made the results up. There was no earthing on any of the Class 1 metal light fittings. What the previous owner </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">had done was just unbelievable. There were bundles of wires which when I started to inspect, had conductors falling out of connector blocks. Not a single earth cable was sleeved</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt"> or connected to the metal light fittings.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">This was just the tip of the iceber</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">g there and since starting my business two years ago, I am appalled at how weak the industry is in terms of ensuring a robust framework which sets out to increase electrical safety and promote the electrical industry in a positive way.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">This is just the mo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">st recent case and certainly not an isolated case. In fact I believe that as little as 10% or less of electrical installation work is compliant. And don’t think new houses are any different. I have worked on brand new houses with problems.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">We are not Pain</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">ters and Decorators, we are not carpenters. Electricians should be highly skilled and competent people entrusted to deliver safe and robust installations.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">In terms of people being aware of Part P and what it’s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt"> there for, I’d</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt"> say less than 2% of people</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt"> understand Part P with probably around 60% falling in to the I need</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt"> a certificate</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt"> category and the remainder just either not caring or knowing.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">I would also like to touch on another factor since you are also looking to understand the competence of the in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">dustry as a whole.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">Let’s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt"> take the ECS scheme. Sounds great right? I am an approved electrician with the JIB and have an ECS card which states my grading as an approved electrician.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">This surely means I am competent? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">Wrong. The JIB takes no account of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">experience and most importantly, your personal skill set.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">I have met plenty of JIB approved electricians who don’t understand basic electrical principles.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">Moving away from the Part P scheme I'd also say that recruitment agencies and employers use the JIB</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">/ECS card scheme exclusively to evaluate ones competence to do the job.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">Useless. But then in an industry that is riddled with incompetence what else can we expect?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">This industry has incompetent leaders and no back bone or frame work to really create an e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">nvironment of excellence. I hope you can take a long hard look</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt"> at things and come up with some positive changes but I won't be expecting any radical changes because in my view this country’s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt"> leaders as a whole are weak and incompetent and that just feeds d</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">own through the entire system.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">Good Luck!</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:right; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:13pt; font-style:italic">3 December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>